[[Disk Mirrornig]] is the [[Replication]] of [[Locical Disk]] volumes onto separate physical [[Hard Disks|Hard Disk Drive]] in [[real time|Real-time computing]] to ensure [[Continuous Availability]].

It is most commonly used in [[RAID 1]].